text.section:
The membership of a Community Health Coalition established under § 13-1008(b) of this subtitle may include:
Representatives of:
A local management board established under Title 8, Subtitle 3 of the Human Services Article;
The local public school system;
Local hospitals, clinics, physicians, and other health care providers;
Local law enforcement;
Local businesses;
Local religious organizations;
Local media;
Institutions of higher education; and
Hospitals and other entities located outside the county that could enhance the county's tobacco use prevention and cessation efforts; and
Any other person that the local health officer believes would help the county meet the tobacco use prevention and cessation goals and requirements established for the county under § 13-1007 of this subtitle.
